profile_positions.description:
Upon my return to South Africa in 2011, I developed a small, specialist part-time private practice to mostly see people in their homes.  
This involved:
- providing specialist neuropsychological interventions for psychologists in private practice and a multi-disciplinary rehabilitation team (Mayo Clinic);
- supporting people with acquired brain injury (ABI), their families, extended support system and employees with managing the impact of ABI;
-providing an individual psychological service for people who have been diagnosed with Parkinson's disease, multiple sclerosis or who have suffered a cerebral vascular accident (stroke);
- assisting individual care teams to develop strategic interventions for people who are suffering from a degenerative disorder;
- providing a supporting service for teenagers and adults who have previously been diagnosed with Asperger's Syndrome (Autistic Spectrum).
